  <info>
    <title>Switching to the administration mode</title><!-- can be changed via merge
in the assembly -->
    <!-- add author's e-mail -->
    <meta name="maintainer" content="jsindelarova@suse.com" its:translate="no"/>
    <abstract><!-- can be changed via merge in the assembly -->
      <para>
       The topic covers the switching between limited and administrative modes.
      </para>
    </abstract>
  </info>
  <para>
    By default, a regular user can log in to &cockpit; with limited access that does not enable the user to perform administration tasks like managing user accounts, updating the system, and so on.
  </para>
  <para>
    To switch to administrative access, proceed as follows:
  </para>
  <procedure>
    <step>
      <para>
        Click the <guimenu>Limited access</guimenu> button.
      </para>
    </step>
    <step>
      <para>
        Fill in the &rootuser; password.
      </para>
    </step>
    <step>
      <para>
        Click <guimenu>Authenticate</guimenu> to confirm.
      </para>
    </step>
  </procedure>
  <para>
    To turn off administrative mode, proceed as follows:
   </para>
  <procedure>
    <step>
      <para>
        Click <guimenu>Administrative access</guimenu>.
      </para>
    </step>
    <step>
      <para>
        To confirm, click <guimenu>Limit access</guimenu>.
      </para>
    </step>
  </procedure>
</topic>
